 {"id": "franken_networkx-addedgesgen", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] add_edges_from(gen_that_reads_self) hits \"Already mutably borrowed\"", "description": "nx internals frequently do `G.add_edges_from(gen)` where gen reads G \u2014 e.g. nx.transitive_closure: `TC.add_edges_from((v, e[1]) for e in nx.edge_bfs(G, v) if e[1] not in TC[v])`. The Rust add_edges_from mutably borrows self's adjacency while iterating the ebunch; the generator's `TC[v]` read needs an immutable borrow on the same RefCell and raises `RuntimeError: Already mutably borrowed`. Fix: Python wrapper for Graph/DiGraph.add_edges_from materializes the ebunch into a list before handing it to Rust, so the generator fully evaluates (reading self) before any mutable borrow starts.", "status": "closed", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T07:47:02.013671Z", "close_reason": "Fixed: _add_edges_from_materialized wraps Graph/DiGraph.add_edges_from to list() the ebunch first. 3 regression tests cover the nx.transitive_closure end-to-end case + the underlying mutably-borrowed pattern.", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T07:47:02.013671Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T07:47:02.013671Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-adjkset", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] AdjacencyView.keys() returns plain iterator \u2014 breaks nx.non_neighbors set arithmetic", "description": "nx.non_neighbors does `graph._adj.keys() - graph._adj[node].keys() - {node}` expecting dict_keys-like views with set-operator support. fnx's _adjacency_view_keys returned a plain `iter(self)` generator, so the subtraction raised TypeError: unsupported operand type(s) for -. This broke many nx algorithms that use non_neighbors internally, including approximation.clique_removal and ramsey.ramsey_R2. Fix: _adjacency_view_keys now returns a _AdjKeysView wrapping a collections.abc.KeysView around a list snapshot, so -, |, &, ^ all work.", "status": "closed", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T07:52:51.336735Z", "close_reason": "Fixed: _adjacency_view_keys returns a KeysView subclass with full set-operator support. Applied to AdjacencyView, MultiAdjacencyView, AtlasView, _GRAPH_ADJACENCY_VIEW_TYPE, _DIGRAPH_ADJACENCY_VIEW_TYPE, and EdgeView types.", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T07:52:51.336735Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T07:52:51.336735Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-grattrset", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] G.graph = {...} assignment raises AttributeError \u2014 breaks nx.subgraph_view", "description": "nx internals (subgraph_view, restricted_view, relabel) do `newG.graph = G.graph` but fnx Graph.graph is a read-only getset_descriptor. _GraphAttrsDescriptor adds a __set__ that clears+updates the existing dict in place.", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T07:59:34.819022Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T07:59:34.819022Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0, "closed_at": "2026-04-24T07:59:34.819022Z", "close_reason": "Fixed in cycle-8."}
-{"id": "franken_networkx-adjprivset", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] _node/_adj assignment AttributeError blocks nx.subgraph_view pipeline", "description": "After br-grattrset fixed the .graph setter, nx.subgraph_view then tries `newG._node = FilterAtlas(...)`. fnx._node is a read-only property. Making it settable alone is insufficient because fnx.Graph.__iter__ reads the Rust storage directly, bypassing any user-set override \u2014 so FilterAtlas-based filtering would not work. Proper fix requires Rust-side Graph to support external adjacency/node storage. Queued.", "status": "open", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T07:59:34.819022Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T07:59:34.819022Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
+{"id": "franken_networkx-adjprivset", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] _node/_adj assignment AttributeError blocks nx.subgraph_view pipeline", "description": "After br-grattrset fixed the .graph setter, nx.subgraph_view then tries `newG._node = FilterAtlas(...)`. fnx._node is a read-only property. Making it settable alone is insufficient because fnx.Graph.__iter__ reads the Rust storage directly, bypassing any user-set override \u2014 so FilterAtlas-based filtering would not work. Proper fix requires Rust-side Graph to support external adjacency/node storage. Queued.", "status": "in_progress", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T07:59:34.819022Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T10:14:00.000000Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-adjcp", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] AdjacencyView lacks copy() \u2014 nx.to_dict_of_dicts breaks on fnx MultiGraph", "description": "Earlier br-atlascp added copy() to AtlasView. MultiGraph's inner adjacency uses AdjacencyView (G.adj[u] -> dict-of-keyed-attrs); it also lacked copy(), so nx.to_dict_of_dicts(fnx_multigraph) crashed with AttributeError: 'AdjacencyView' object has no attribute 'copy'. Added copy() to AdjacencyView (returns dict-of-dicts snapshot) and to MultiAdjacencyView (returns dict-of-dicts-of-dicts recursively).", "status": "closed", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T08:08:51.243295Z", "close_reason": "Fixed: AdjacencyView.copy() and MultiAdjacencyView.copy() return plain dict-snapshot structures. 3 regression tests cover nx.to_dict_of_dicts on fnx MultiGraph + direct copy() calls.", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T08:08:51.243295Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T08:08:51.243295Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-classpred", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] Graph.is_directed(None) raises \u2014 nx generators with create_using=fnx.Graph fail", "description": "nx.utils.misc.check_create_using does `G.is_directed(None) if isinstance(G, type) else G.is_directed()` when deciding whether a create_using CLASS matches expected directedness. On nx, these are plain methods that ignore self, so self=None works. fnx's Rust descriptors require a real instance and raise TypeError: 'descriptor is_directed for franken_networkx.Graph objects doesn't apply to a NoneType object'. This broke nx.gnp_random_graph, nx.barabasi_albert_graph, and any nx generator with create_using=fnx.Graph. Fix: _make_class_safe_predicate wraps is_directed / is_multigraph so class-level calls return the class-level default and instance calls still delegate to the Rust descriptor.", "status": "closed", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T08:13:35.291148Z", "close_reason": "Fixed: class-level is_directed/is_multigraph wrappers applied to all 4 graph classes. 6 regression tests in TestClassLevelPredicates cover class/instance paths + end-to-end nx generators with fnx create_using.", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T08:13:35.291148Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T08:13:35.291148Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-rmvbunch", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] remove_edges_from/remove_nodes_from(gen_reading_self) hits \"Already mutably borrowed\"", "description": "nx internals call `g.remove_edges_from(nx.selfloop_edges(g))` and `g.remove_nodes_from(iterator_reading_g)` \u2014 e.g. nx.community.girvan_newman does exactly this. The Rust remove_*_from mutably borrows self while iterating the bunch; the generator's read of self._adj needs an immutable borrow and raises `RuntimeError: Already mutably borrowed`. Same class as br-addedgesgen \u2014 fix by materializing the bunch before the Rust call.", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T08:24:00.808208Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T08:24:00.808208Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0, "closed_at": "2026-04-24T08:24:00.808208Z", "close_reason": "Fixed in cycle-9: _remove_bunch_materialized wrapper on Graph/DiGraph/MultiGraph/MultiDiGraph remove_edges_from and remove_nodes_from."}
